# Roguebusters — Project Notes

## Current State (as of March 2026)

The game runs. Core loop is functional: procedural city generation, turn-based movement,
NPC hostile pursuit, melee/ranged combat, inventory, and pick-up/drop/wield items.

**Recent changes:**
- Tileset switched to `tilesets/latest.png` (16×16 custom tileset)
- Window is resizable via a patched local copy of bracket-terminal in `vendor/bracket-terminal/`
  (two-line fix: `init.rs` makes window resizable when `resize_scaling` is set; `mainloop.rs`
  calls `change_physical_size` instead of `change_physical_size_smooth` to avoid letterboxing)
- `ScreenService` is now dynamic — updated each tick from `ctx.get_char_size()`; UI panels
  adapt when the window is resized
- UI box borders switched from mixed double/single (`LINES_DOUBLE_SINGLE`) to consistent
  single-line (`LINES_SINGLE`) to fix jagged corners
- `NPCBehavior` system added — hostile NPCs chase the player and attack when adjacent
- Testing framework added under `src/testing/` (behind `#[cfg(any(test, feature="testing"))]`)

## Active Work Plan

Seven streams — see the plan file for full details. Rough priority order:

1. **Building entrance orientation** (prerequisite for interior variety)
   — Add `entrance_wall` to `Space`; implement prefab alignment in `fill_space`

2. **NPC AI state machine**
   — Wire up `src/systems/ai/npc_update.rs`; implement Searching / Fleeing states

3. **Building interior variety**
   — Randomise generator per building; add speakeasy / shop / apartment / office generators

4. **Dialog system** — `E` key opens a dialog modal with the nearest NPC

5. **Shops** — `Shopkeeper` component; shop modal with buy/sell; spawn in shop buildings

6. **Item glyph reindex** — See `notes/item-glyphs.md` for the full reference table.
   Most items share glyph indices that don't match the new tileset; user will update
   `tilesets/latest.png` via the composer and then update `<char>` values in XML.

7. **README update** — Rewrite once the above features are in

## Key Decisions & Constraints

- **`BuildingOrientation::Vertical` / `Horizontal`** `todo!()` stubs will NOT be implemented
  for now. Triple-style building footprints are also deferred.
- **No rayon / parallel specs** — project is intentionally single-threaded for now; the
  architecture supports adding it later via `par_join`.
- **vendor/bracket-terminal** is a local patch of bracket-terminal 0.8.7. Do not update it
  from crates.io without re-applying the two patches in `init.rs` and `mainloop.rs`.
- `src/input/service.rs` is dead/stub code — do not use it; `src/input/handlers.rs` is the
  active input path.
- The `src/systems/ai/` folder exists but is **not in the module tree** yet (`main.rs` does
  not declare `pub mod ai`). It will be wired in as part of the AI stream.

